                              <item xml:id="q5" n="5">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">10</dim>
                                 <locus from="33" to="42" facs="033">Fols 33–42</locus>
                                 <note>
                                    <locus target="#37 #38" facs="037 038">Folss. 37, 38, </locus> are narrower than the other folios by about 1 cm. Stubs appear between <locus target="#37 #38" facs="038">37, 38, </locus> and between <locus target="#38 #39" facs="039">38, 39</locus>.</note>
                              Quire 5:
                              6, stub after 5
                              5, stub after 6
                            </item>
                              <item xml:id="q6" n="6">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">8</dim>
                                 <locus from="43" to="50" facs="043">Fols 43–50</locus>
                              Quire 6
                            </item>
                              <item xml:id="q7" n="7">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">5</dim>
                                 <locus from="51" to="55" facs="051">Fols 51–55</locus>
                                 <note>The first three folios of this quire have been cut off very near to the gutter. The next 15 folios or so are worn and tattered in the lower gutter side of the folios. The wear patterns suggest that this was the beginning of a book and exposed to wear from the outside. There are various and sundry threads visible in the next several folios that stitch folios to one another. All of this would suggest that the codex is composite with folios from two different sources.</note>
                              Quire 7:
                              5, stub before 1
                              4, stub before 1
                              3, stub before 1
                            </item>
                              <item xml:id="q8" n="8">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">7</dim>
                                 <locus from="56" to="62" facs="056">Fols 56–62</locus>
                                 <note>The remnant of a folio stub is visible between <locus target="#60 #61" facs="061">fols. 60, 61</locus>.</note>
                              Quire 8:
                              3, stub after 5
                            </item>
                              <item xml:id="q9" n="9">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">8</dim>
                                 <locus from="63" to="70" facs="063">Fols 63–70</locus>
                                 <note>Beginning at <locus target="#64v" facs="065">fols. 64v, </locus> and extending through <locus target="#83" facs="083">83, </locus>
                                 (and beyond) there is a small “burn trench” along the tops of the folios. Intruding into this pattern is <locus target="#71" facs="071">71, </locus>
                                 that does not have the burn pattern. <locus target="#70" facs="070">70, </locus> is stitched to <locus target="#69" facs="069">69</locus> with pink thread.</note>
                              Quire 9
                            </item>
                              <item xml:id="q10" n="10">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">8</dim>
                                 <locus from="71" to="78" facs="071">Fols 71–78</locus>
                                 <note>
                                    <locus target="#71 #78" facs="071 078">Folss. 71, 78, </locus> are stitched to <locus target="#72 #77" facs="072 077">72, 77</locus>, respectively.</note>
                              Quire 10
                            </item>
                              <item xml:id="q11" n="11">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">8</dim>
                                 <locus from="79" to="86" facs="079">Fols 79–86</locus>
                              Quire 11
                            </item>
                              <item xml:id="q12" n="12">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">9</dim>
                                 <locus from="87" to="95" facs="087">Fols 87–95</locus>
                                 <note>
                                    <locus target="#87" facs="087">Fol. 87</locus> appears to be connected as a regular part of the folio,
                                    but an object can be run between either side (suggesting the open space between two folios). We judge it to be an individual folio.</note>
                              Quire 12:
                              1 added
                            </item>
                              <item xml:id="q13" n="13">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">6</dim>
                                 <locus from="96" to="101" facs="096">Fols 96–101</locus>
                              Quire 13
                            </item>
                              <item xml:id="q14" n="14">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">8</dim>
                                 <locus from="102" to="109" facs="102">Fols 102–109</locus>
                              Quire 14
                            </item>
                              <item xml:id="q15" n="15">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">8</dim>
                                 <locus from="110" to="117" facs="110">Fols 110–117</locus>
                              Quire 15
                            </item>
                              <item xml:id="q16" n="16">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">6</dim>
                                 <locus from="118" to="123" facs="118">Fols 118–123</locus>
                                 <note>Stubs appear between <locus target="#119 #120" facs="120">folss. 119, 120, </locus> and between <locus target="#122 #123" facs="123">122, 123</locus>.</note>
                              Quire 16:
                              2, stub after 5
                              5, stub after 2
                            </item>
                          </list>
