                        <item xml:id="e5">
                          <locus target="#22r" facs="022"> f. 22r, line 14</locus>
                           <desc>Overlooked words of text are written in the upper margin with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e6">
                           <desc>
                          The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line.
                          Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex
                          combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long,
                          the scribe completes the line of text above the end of the line (throughout)
                        </desc>
